other_tests.findings: Increased echogenicity of the liver consistent with fatty infiltration. No focal masses are noted. The gallbladder contains several stones, no gallbladder wall thickening, no edema, gallbladder not dilated, small septation seen at the fundus. Common bile duct not visualized due to body habitus, no signs of biliary obstruction as intrahepatic biliary ducts are not dilated. The pancreas is not well visualized due to body habitus. The spleen is normal in size with 8.3 cm.
